senses.sense_definition: Happening once every five years or lasting for a period of five years.

examples.text: The committee published its <w>quinquennial</w> report on the state of the environment.
We are preparing for the <w>quinquennial</w> census that updates our national statistics.

senses.sense_definition: A period of five years; a synonym of <w>quinquennium</w>.

examples.text: The economic plan was designed to achieve specific goals within the first <w>quinquennial</w>.
Historians analyzed the changes that occurred during that specific <w>quinquennial</w>.
The couple celebrated their <w>quinquennial</w> with a quiet dinner at home.
Members gathered to mark the <w>quinquennial</w> of the society's founding.

senses.sense_definition: A festival or religious ritual held in the fifth year of a Roman emperor's reign; a synonym of <w>quinquennalia</w>.

examples.text: The emperor announced a grand <w>quinquennial</w> to honor the gods.
Citizens from across the empire traveled to Rome for the <w>quinquennial</w> games.
